WEBVTT

1
00:01:12.824 --> 00:01:14.409
[John] <i>We got off to a rough start.</i>

2
00:01:16.036 --> 00:01:17.037
<i>It happens.</i>

3
00:01:19.539 --> 00:01:20.707
<i>With cases like this.</i>

4
00:01:23.793 --> 00:01:25.170
<i>Missing rich girl.</i>

5
00:01:25.170 --> 00:01:26.630
<i>Dead guy in the trunk.</i>

6
00:01:33.303 --> 00:01:36.014
<i>Then me. with all my. um... I don't know...</i>

7
00:01:36.598 --> 00:01:37.599
<i>issues.</i>

8
00:01:41.228 --> 00:01:42.229
<i>I'm not being modest.</i>

9
00:01:42.854 --> 00:01:44.689
<i>I'm really good at what I do.</i>

10
00:01:44.689 --> 00:01:47.609
<i>And a man like Jonathan Siegel
wouldn't have called me otherwise.</i>

11
00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:50.987
<i>I just needed a moment to settle in.</i>

12
00:01:51.905 --> 00:01:54.991
<i>Anyway. back to business.</i>

13
00:02:19.224 --> 00:02:20.767
<i>Bernie Siegel.</i>

14
00:02:21.434 --> 00:02:24.396
<i>Olivia's father and former husband
to the late Rachel Kaye.</i>

15
00:02:24.980 --> 00:02:28.149
<i>Also a movie producer.
although not in his father's class.</i>

16
00:02:28.149 --> 00:02:31.570
Please. call me Bernie.
Hey. I love this place.

17
00:02:31.570 --> 00:02:34.239
[John] <i>His last big hit was
about a surfing monkey.</i>

18
00:02:34.239 --> 00:02:35.574
It's. uh. class.

19
00:02:35.574 --> 00:02:37.450
When I'm in town.
I won't stay anywhere else.

20
00:02:37.450 --> 00:02:40.120
Yeah. a man of discerning taste.
I appreciate that.

21
00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:41.788
[server]
Yes. gentlemen. What would you like?

22
00:02:41.788 --> 00:02:44.082
Two slices of white toast.
Side of cottage cheese.

23
00:02:44.082 --> 00:02:46.960
- A pot of hot water with lemon.
- Just coffee. Black.

24
00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:49.170
[chuckles]
What I really want is bacon and eggs.

25
00:02:49.170 --> 00:02:50.964
but I'm on what they call a bland diet.

26
00:02:51.715 --> 00:02:53.884
Anyway. what can I do for you?

27
00:02:54.426 --> 00:02:55.886
I'd like to talk about Olivia.

28
00:02:56.469 --> 00:02:59.139
Yeah. I gotta tell you. Sugar.

29
00:02:59.139 --> 00:03:02.142
[stammers] I think you're wasting
your time and my father's money.

30
00:03:02.642 --> 00:03:07.147
Olivia will come back any day now.
Just like she always does.

31
00:03:07.147 --> 00:03:08.857
Ready to go to rehab again.

32
00:03:09.983 --> 00:03:11.943
If I was her father.
I'd find that concerning.

33
00:03:11.943 --> 00:03:13.194
You're not. and I don't.

34
00:03:13.778 --> 00:03:15.363
- Your father does.
- [Bernie clicks tongue]

35
00:03:15.363 --> 00:03:16.698
[server] And here we are.

36
00:03:18.366 --> 00:03:19.868
[Bernie] I'll tell you something.

37
00:03:19.868 --> 00:03:24.205
I know Olivia better than anyone.
Certainly better than my father.

38
00:03:24.873 --> 00:03:27.834
[scoffs] And I know her
a hell of a lot better than Melanie.

39
00:03:27.834 --> 00:03:29.336
I'll tell you that.

40
00:03:29.336 --> 00:03:31.546
You had quite a time
with her last night. didn't you?

41
00:03:32.547 --> 00:03:35.759
I'm a little upset about that.
I have to say. I mean. she is my ex-wife.

42
00:03:36.593 --> 00:03:39.346
Oh. you didn't know that. did you.
Mr. Private Investigator?

43
00:03:39.346 --> 00:03:42.599
{\an8}You and Melanie Matthews were married
in Las Vegas. Nevada

44
00:03:42.599 --> 00:03:43.934
on New Year's Eve 1999.

45
00:03:43.934 --> 00:03:46.519
Three days later you were both arrested
for malicious destruction of property.

46
00:03:46.519 --> 00:03:48.396
possession of narcotics.
drunk and disorderly conduct.

47
00:03:48.396 --> 00:03:50.106
and discharge of a firearm. [chuckles]

48
00:03:50.106 --> 00:03:53.151
Hmm. It was a hell of a honeymoon.

49
00:03:57.197 --> 00:03:58.865
Please. Discreetly.

50
00:04:03.036 --> 00:04:04.162
Where did you get this?

51
00:04:05.830 --> 00:04:09.209
That type of Polaroid film
was introduced in 1996.

52
00:04:11.044 --> 00:04:13.296
You were married to Rachel Kaye then.
weren't you?

53
00:04:15.382 --> 00:04:16.382
You know I was.

54
00:04:18.009 --> 00:04:19.511
Did you take that photograph?

55
00:04:24.432 --> 00:04:25.433
No. I did not.

56
00:04:26.142 --> 00:04:29.229
Thank you for telling me the truth.
Bernie. I appreciate it.

57
00:04:29.229 --> 00:04:33.608
Mm-hmm. [smacks lips] Hmm.

58
00:04:34.943 --> 00:04:38.530
Did you ever love someone?
I mean. really love them?

59
00:04:39.114 --> 00:04:40.865
Like if the grim reaper came
to you and said.

60
00:04:40.865 --> 00:04:43.159
"I'm gonna take the life of this person

61
00:04:43.159 --> 00:04:46.454
that you love
unless you give me your life."

62
00:04:49.291 --> 00:04:52.085
Well. I would have. For Rachel.

63
00:04:54.963 --> 00:04:56.840
And Olivia's all I got left of her.

64
00:04:58.341 --> 00:05:02.554
And if you think that I don't care
about my daughter. you fuck.

65
00:05:03.305 --> 00:05:05.307
then fuck you and fuck off.

66
00:05:05.307 --> 00:05:08.560
And I'm paying for your fucking coffee.

67
00:05:09.269 --> 00:05:10.270
Thank you.

68
00:05:13.815 --> 00:05:17.110
[John] <i>He's hiding something.
Or at least I hit a nerve.</i>

69
00:05:18.778 --> 00:05:21.990
<i>I mean. being told to fuck off is usually
a sign of progress.</i>

70
00:05:49.726 --> 00:05:50.977
[metal clanks]

71
00:05:52.437 --> 00:05:55.190
[John] <i>Davy Siegel and Kenny.
his guy Friday.</i>

72
00:06:00.028 --> 00:06:01.821
- <i>Let's be quick. huh?</i>
- [Kenny] <i>Yeah.</i>

73
00:06:03.156 --> 00:06:04.824
- [David] <i>You check in here?</i>
- <i>Check the bedroom.</i>

74
00:06:07.244 --> 00:06:10.205
[David] <i>Hey. uh. uh. uh. get the. uh.
listening device going.</i>

75
00:06:10.205 --> 00:06:11.164
<i>Copy that.</i>

76
00:06:11.164 --> 00:06:14.292
[John] <i>Spying on the person hired
to find his sister.</i>

77
00:06:14.292 --> 00:06:17.754
<i>Why would he do that? What's he afraid of?</i>

78
00:06:19.422 --> 00:06:21.258
[David] <i>Hey. uh. uh. uh...</i>

79
00:06:21.258 --> 00:06:22.384
[Kenny] <i>Find anything?</i>

80
00:06:22.384 --> 00:06:26.054
[David]
<i>Yeah. but... Just some weird magazines...</i>

81
00:06:26.054 --> 00:06:27.138
- [beeps]
- <i>...or whatever. Noth...</i>

82
00:06:27.138 --> 00:06:28.306
- <i>There's no wallet. There's no...</i>
- [chuckles]

83
00:06:28.306 --> 00:06:30.976
- [John] <i>It helps when they're stupid.</i>
- [David] <i>Hold on. I got some letters.</i>

84
00:06:30.976 --> 00:06:33.144
[Kenny] <i>Well. bring 'em here.
Let me take some photos.</i>

85
00:06:34.896 --> 00:06:39.568
[John] <i>It's not always as much fun.
but helps move things along.</i>

86
00:06:40.151 --> 00:06:42.737
- [Kenny] <i>Got ourselves a cinephile.</i>
- [John] Hey. Helen. It's me.

87
00:06:42.737 --> 00:06:45.073
- [David] <i>Yeah. we do.</i>
- Someone's gonna call you.

88
00:06:45.073 --> 00:06:46.741
They want to talk to my mom.

89
00:06:46.741 --> 00:06:48.326
Obviously they think that's you.

90
00:06:49.452 --> 00:06:50.829
God bless paper trails.

91
00:06:52.581 --> 00:06:54.749
They're on their way. Uh-huh.

92
00:06:58.253 --> 00:07:01.298
<i>Just because I could see Davy coming
doesn't mean he isn't dangerous.</i>

93
00:07:01.298 --> 00:07:04.092
<i>I can't have him digging into my past.
for one thing.</i>

94
00:07:04.092 --> 00:07:06.011
<i>No. that won't do at all.</i>

95
00:07:06.011 --> 00:07:09.639
<i>With Bernie being no help and Davy being
something even less than that.</i>

96
00:07:09.639 --> 00:07:12.309
<i>hopefully I can get some leads
talking to Olivia's friends.</i>

97
00:07:12.309 --> 00:07:14.227
<i>You know. just like in the movies.</i>

98
00:07:14.227 --> 00:07:16.313
[Olivia's friend] The first time
we got high was. like. sixth grade.

99
00:07:16.313 --> 00:07:17.647
Sixth grade? How old?

100
00:07:17.647 --> 00:07:18.982
- [friend scoffs] Like. 11.
- Wow.

101
00:07:18.982 --> 00:07:20.901
- [friend chuckles]
- But we haven't hung out with her

102
00:07:20.901 --> 00:07:21.985
in almost a year.

103
00:07:22.694 --> 00:07:23.695
Because she was sober?

104
00:07:23.695 --> 00:07:25.697
Why do you think she was getting sober?

105
00:07:25.697 --> 00:07:28.992
Was she using more than anyone else
or drinking more?

106
00:07:28.992 --> 00:07:33.288
Yeah. I think she started
to get a little out of control.

107
00:07:33.288 --> 00:07:36.291
- Are you sure?
- You should have seen her in her heyday.

108
00:07:36.291 --> 00:07:39.127
She did some shit
that would have landed most kids in jail.

109
00:07:39.127 --> 00:07:40.086
Like what?

110
00:07:40.086 --> 00:07:42.380
- A lot of drugs. dude. [chuckles]
- [chuckles] Okay.

111
00:07:42.380 --> 00:07:44.883
But I think she had. like.
a life-changing moment

112
00:07:44.883 --> 00:07:46.843
that just kind of freaked her out.

113
00:07:48.261 --> 00:07:51.264
[John] Do you know anything
about her romantic life? Boyfriends?

114
00:07:52.015 --> 00:07:52.849
No.

115
00:07:52.849 --> 00:07:54.392
You're not lying to me. are you. sunshine?

116
00:07:55.101 --> 00:07:56.770
[John] You remember her being with him?

117
00:07:56.770 --> 00:07:58.188
No. not that I could recall.

118
00:07:58.188 --> 00:07:59.773
Nothing regular? No guy she saw?

119
00:07:59.773 --> 00:08:01.608
- Not the way we were partying.
- Oh. yeah?

120
00:08:01.608 --> 00:08:04.694
It was a different guy all the time.
You know how it goes.

121
00:08:05.362 --> 00:08:07.322
I would have no idea.
but I... I trust what you say.

122
00:08:08.448 --> 00:08:10.033
- Hey. John Sugar.
- [friend 2] Hey.

123
00:08:10.033 --> 00:08:11.576
Did you ever see her with this guy?

124
00:08:11.576 --> 00:08:13.203
- Never saw him.
- You sure?

125
00:08:13.203 --> 00:08:17.540
Positive. She only buys from me.
She hasn't bought in a long time.

126
00:08:18.041 --> 00:08:20.835
- Like months. weeks? What's a long time?
- I don't know. At least a year. man.

127
00:08:21.962 --> 00:08:24.589
What about you guys?
You still doing drugs? What's going on?

128
00:08:25.173 --> 00:08:27.467
[chuckles] I'm finishing my degree.

129
00:08:27.467 --> 00:08:29.177
- I'm gonna... I've gotten it together.
- You are?

130
00:08:29.177 --> 00:08:30.887
- You?
- No comment.

131
00:08:30.887 --> 00:08:31.846
- I thought so.
- [friend laughs]

132
00:08:31.846 --> 00:08:35.267
Okay. Well. if you think of anything else.
call this number. Thank you.

133
00:08:35.267 --> 00:08:37.644
- <i>Thanks for taking the time. All right.</i>
- [friend 3] <i>Yeah. Of course.</i>

134
00:08:37.644 --> 00:08:40.522
[John] <i>Sounds like Olivia really
had moved on from her old life.</i>

135
00:08:40.522 --> 00:08:41.606
<i>That's the good news.</i>

136
00:08:42.649 --> 00:08:45.151
<i>The bad news is her new life.</i>

137
00:08:45.151 --> 00:08:48.530
<i>well. it somehow seems to have gotten
her into even worse trouble.</i>

138
00:08:49.864 --> 00:08:53.827
<i>It's time to update Jonathan Siegel.
I got some questions for him too.</i>

139
00:08:55.537 --> 00:08:58.248
<i>The Boy in the Corner</i> was a massive hit.
It was a phenomenon.

140
00:08:58.832 --> 00:09:00.875
<i>The Man in the Corner</i> is gonna be one too.

141
00:09:00.875 --> 00:09:04.087
This is David's big comeback.
and nothing's gonna change that.

142
00:09:05.380 --> 00:09:10.760
If this story comes out.
no studio is gonna release this movie.

143
00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:12.929
and you'll be out 60 million bucks.

144
00:09:13.597 --> 00:09:15.849
You broke the cardinal rule
of producing. Bernie.

145
00:09:15.849 --> 00:09:17.142
You used your own money.

146
00:09:17.642 --> 00:09:19.519
The story's not gonna come out. right?

147
00:09:19.519 --> 00:09:24.274
No. We have signed ironclad NDAs
from seven of the eight victims.

148
00:09:24.274 --> 00:09:25.400
Don't use the word "victim."

149
00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:29.112
But what worries me
is accuser number eight.

150
00:09:29.112 --> 00:09:31.990
[Bernie] Oh. she's a pain in the ass.
but we'll get there. Trust me.

151
00:09:31.990 --> 00:09:33.909
One way or the other. she'll come around.

152
00:09:34.409 --> 00:09:37.329
Well. the other seven certainly feel
you've been generous.

153
00:09:37.329 --> 00:09:41.124
[scoffs] Hold on a second. Bernie.
are you saying that Davy is guilty?

154
00:09:41.124 --> 00:09:42.542
Did I say that. sweetheart?

155
00:09:42.542 --> 00:09:44.586
- He did not say that.
- And it's David.

156
00:09:44.586 --> 00:09:46.254
What if we don't get there
with number eight?

157
00:09:46.254 --> 00:09:48.840
If we don't. then it's he said.
she said. and we'll see her in court.

158
00:09:48.840 --> 00:09:50.175
We'll get there.

159
00:09:50.175 --> 00:09:51.885
[Bernie's wife]
Do not use the word "victim."

160
00:09:51.885 --> 00:09:53.762
No one is to use the word "victim."

161
00:09:54.262 --> 00:09:57.224
- [Ruby] Well. what are you thinking. John?
- [John] I don't know.

162
00:09:57.224 --> 00:09:59.976
I mean.
this Siegel family is something else.

163
00:09:59.976 --> 00:10:02.812
Hmm. Okay. Why?

164
00:10:03.438 --> 00:10:05.023
- You want a drink?
- Uh. no. thanks.

165
00:10:05.732 --> 00:10:08.568
- I went back to see Jonathan again.
- [Ruby] Oh. wow. So?

166
00:10:09.444 --> 00:10:12.322
[John] Since you and I last spoke.
I met a few of your family members.

167
00:10:12.322 --> 00:10:16.326
Oh. I'm sorry about that.
Let me guess. Bernie.

168
00:10:17.285 --> 00:10:19.371
Yeah. He doesn't share your concern

169
00:10:19.371 --> 00:10:21.665
- about Olivia's disappearance.
- [Jonathan] Of course. he doesn't.

170
00:10:21.665 --> 00:10:22.791
- [Ruby] Oh. really?
- Really.

171
00:10:22.791 --> 00:10:26.294
Yeah. he sent his son Davy
and his bodyguard

172
00:10:26.294 --> 00:10:28.046
to snoop around my hotel room

173
00:10:28.046 --> 00:10:30.048
- while we were having breakfast.
- [Ruby] Oh. God.

174
00:10:30.048 --> 00:10:33.051
Olivia is a screwup. She always will be.

175
00:10:33.051 --> 00:10:35.595
That's a narrative
that suits Bernie the best.

176
00:10:36.096 --> 00:10:39.683
Lets him focus on making bad movies
and his idiot son.

177
00:10:39.683 --> 00:10:42.936
Oh. [sighs]
I shouldn't have said that. should I?

178
00:10:42.936 --> 00:10:46.273
Um. not all Bernie's pictures are bad.

179
00:10:46.856 --> 00:10:48.817
- Ouch.
- [chuckles]

180
00:10:48.817 --> 00:10:51.528
David is. uh. Bernie's son
by Margit Sorensen?

181
00:10:52.028 --> 00:10:53.280
- [Jonathan] Have you met her yet?
- No.

182
00:10:53.280 --> 00:10:59.578
[scoffs] Another paradigm
of clawing self-interest. Horrible woman.

183
00:11:01.371 --> 00:11:04.624
I'm sensing yours is not
the closest of families.

184
00:11:08.211 --> 00:11:09.212
Well...

185
00:11:12.257 --> 00:11:14.217
[swallows] ...we have our reasons.

186
00:11:18.388 --> 00:11:20.390
[Ruby] John. do you mind giving me a hand?

187
00:11:20.974 --> 00:11:21.808
Hmm?

188
00:11:22.392 --> 00:11:27.606
Well. we seem to have covered everything
under the sun except for my granddaughter.

189
00:11:27.606 --> 00:11:29.524
Thank you for your patience.

190
00:11:29.524 --> 00:11:30.859
Sorry.

191
00:11:30.859 --> 00:11:33.445
This is a record of the GPS

192
00:11:33.445 --> 00:11:34.362
- from Olivia's car.
- Hmm.

193
00:11:34.362 --> 00:11:36.197
- [Ruby] Oh. come on.
- [John chuckles]

194
00:11:36.197 --> 00:11:37.532
[Ruby] John. sit.

195
00:11:38.033 --> 00:11:40.577
Um. I found that the week
before she disappeared.

196
00:11:40.577 --> 00:11:43.204
she made repeat trips to a location
that caused me concern.

197
00:11:43.705 --> 00:11:46.374
A woman who lived at this address.
Carmen Vasquez.

198
00:11:46.374 --> 00:11:47.751
was raped and murdered recently.

199
00:11:47.751 --> 00:11:50.837
Olivia's car was there the night
that Miss Vasquez was killed.

200
00:11:50.837 --> 00:11:53.673
And this may have something
to do with the death

201
00:11:53.673 --> 00:11:55.383
<i>of the man who killed Miss Vasquez.</i>

202
00:11:55.383 --> 00:11:56.676
Why would you think that?

203
00:11:57.928 --> 00:12:01.014
[John] Because his body is in the trunk
of Olivia's car right now.

204
00:12:04.935 --> 00:12:05.936
Shit.

205
00:12:09.481 --> 00:12:10.857
[John] <i>Clifford Carter.</i>

206
00:12:11.399 --> 00:12:13.693
<i>Arrests for assault. rape
and human trafficking.</i>

207
00:12:13.693 --> 00:12:14.778
[Ruby] John.

208
00:12:14.778 --> 00:12:17.572
[John] <i>Now lying dead in the car
of missing Hollywood royalty.</i>

209
00:12:18.073 --> 00:12:19.324
Sit. [sighs]

210
00:12:20.158 --> 00:12:20.992
[sighs]

211
00:12:20.992 --> 00:12:22.619
[John]
I'm obligated to report to the police

212
00:12:22.619 --> 00:12:25.080
the discovery of any homicide victim.
Mr. Siegel.

213
00:12:25.080 --> 00:12:27.040
You haven't though. have you?

214
00:12:29.918 --> 00:12:32.629
I'm gonna pretend like
I never opened the trunk of that car.

215
00:12:32.629 --> 00:12:34.214
I'd appreciate it.

216
00:12:34.214 --> 00:12:36.841
But still.
I feel that her life could be in danger.

217
00:12:37.342 --> 00:12:38.969
- Jesus. God.
- Yeah.

218
00:12:38.969 --> 00:12:40.053
[Ruby] John.

219
00:12:40.720 --> 00:12:43.431
There's a lot going on. It's...
These people. you know. these places.

220
00:12:43.431 --> 00:12:44.891
<i>I-I should be narrowing things down
by now...</i>

221
00:12:44.891 --> 00:12:47.310
- [Ruby] <i>Sit.</i>
- <i>...but the case just keeps growing.</i>

222
00:12:47.310 --> 00:12:48.478
To me the question is

223
00:12:48.478 --> 00:12:50.522
there a connection
between Olivia's disappearance

224
00:12:50.522 --> 00:12:55.527
- and whatever else is going on with this...
- [Ruby] Okay. [sighs] That's what I mean.

225
00:12:57.529 --> 00:12:58.613
What?

226
00:13:00.156 --> 00:13:02.409
Nothing. Missed you. Sugar.

227
00:13:03.785 --> 00:13:04.786
I missed you too.

228
00:13:05.453 --> 00:13:07.872
Yeah.
Which is why I thought it would be nice

229
00:13:07.872 --> 00:13:10.875
for us to enjoy one another's company.

230
00:13:10.875 --> 00:13:13.587
- Ah. The case. Okay. Okay.
- Can we do that? Can we just enjoy

231
00:13:13.587 --> 00:13:15.005
- each other's company...
- Sure.

232
00:13:15.005 --> 00:13:16.590
- ...and eat together?
- Sure. Let's...

233
00:13:17.090 --> 00:13:18.758
- Let's give it a shot. shall we?
- Okay.

234
00:13:21.469 --> 00:13:25.473
- [chewing] This was a great idea.
- Mm-hmm.

235
00:13:25.473 --> 00:13:28.184
- Lunch. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

236
00:13:28.894 --> 00:13:31.521
- How've you been?
- Good. Busy.

237
00:13:31.521 --> 00:13:33.064
- Look at you.
- [chuckles]

238
00:13:33.064 --> 00:13:34.357
I bet chef extraordinaire.

239
00:13:34.357 --> 00:13:35.692
- More than 15 of us you manage now?
- [chuckles]

240
00:13:35.692 --> 00:13:37.027
Even though there was no cooking involved.

241
00:13:37.027 --> 00:13:39.487
- Nineteen.
- Wow. 19. huh? Hmm.

242
00:13:39.487 --> 00:13:40.864
- Bye. Mirembe.
- [chuckles]

243
00:13:42.782 --> 00:13:45.285
[John] Just. before I forget.
I already called Charlie.

244
00:13:45.285 --> 00:13:48.997
- you know. to help with surveillance.
- Wow. Without consulting me?

245
00:13:49.831 --> 00:13:50.832
I was being proactive.

246
00:13:50.832 --> 00:13:55.253
Ah. proactive. Okay. Well. remember.
you have to keep a low profile.

247
00:13:55.253 --> 00:13:56.880
I know. I know.

248
00:14:01.676 --> 00:14:03.303
Okay. How often does that happen?

249
00:14:03.303 --> 00:14:05.555
[grunts] It's good.

250
00:14:06.139 --> 00:14:07.682
Have you called Dr. Vickers?

251
00:14:07.682 --> 00:14:09.976
- I've thought about it.
- John.

252
00:14:09.976 --> 00:14:12.896
I'll see him at the meeting tomorrow.
I'll talk to him then. Okay?

253
00:14:12.896 --> 00:14:15.273
No. not okay. Call him today.

254
00:14:15.273 --> 00:14:16.983
[engine starts]

255
00:14:19.569 --> 00:14:22.113
It's good. Thanks for lunch.

256
00:14:25.283 --> 00:14:28.286
[John] <i>Ruby likes to worry.
and I love her for it.</i>

257
00:14:29.329 --> 00:14:30.538
<i>But I've got work to do.</i>

258
00:14:32.165 --> 00:14:35.252
<i>Right now the best link I have
to finding Olivia is Melanie Matthews.</i>

259
00:14:35.252 --> 00:14:39.256
<i>which is convenient because she called
and said she'd like to meet.</i>

260
00:14:40.924 --> 00:14:42.467
[Melanie] Hi. I'm Melanie.

261
00:14:42.467 --> 00:14:44.094
[group] Hi. Melanie.

262
00:14:44.094 --> 00:14:45.387
I'm an alcoholic.

263
00:14:46.888 --> 00:14:48.932
I haven't been to a meeting
in a long time.

264
00:14:48.932 --> 00:14:54.646
And I mean a long time.
I was 23 years sober.

265
00:14:56.898 --> 00:14:59.401
But as of two weeks ago.
I started drinking like a fish.

266
00:15:00.902 --> 00:15:04.573
But that all ended last...
[breathes shakily] ...night.

267
00:15:04.573 --> 00:15:08.535
'Cause last night I brought
a total stranger into my house.

268
00:15:08.535 --> 00:15:13.081
and that's something I haven't done
since I was in my 20s.

269
00:15:15.083 --> 00:15:19.379
But because I was fucked-up.
I brought a stranger into my home.

270
00:15:24.342 --> 00:15:27.095
I think the reason we get fucked-up
is simple.

271
00:15:28.138 --> 00:15:29.890
- [John] <i>They're lonely.</i>
- We're lonely.

272
00:15:34.936 --> 00:15:36.271
[Melanie] <i>And we're afraid.</i>

273
00:15:39.482 --> 00:15:41.985
And here we live in a world
with millions of people

274
00:15:41.985 --> 00:15:45.280
all with the capacity to love
and be loved. and somehow...

275
00:15:45.280 --> 00:15:49.284
[breathes shakily]
<i>...we just can't get our shit together.</i>

276
00:15:49.284 --> 00:15:51.703
<i>And I think it's because we're afraid.</i>

277
00:15:53.413 --> 00:15:57.500
We've been hurt in the past.
and we don't want to be hurt again.

278
00:15:57.500 --> 00:16:01.338
<i>So... we get fucked-up.</i>

279
00:16:03.048 --> 00:16:05.050
<i>make bad choices</i>

280
00:16:05.050 --> 00:16:07.427
<i>and settle for any kind of connection
we can find.</i>

281
00:16:10.513 --> 00:16:12.182
But you know what happened last night?

282
00:16:13.683 --> 00:16:16.561
The guy didn't hurt me.
He didn't steal from me.

283
00:16:16.561 --> 00:16:21.316
He didn't even fuck me. even though
at the time I told him I wanted him to.

284
00:16:23.026 --> 00:16:24.152
No. You know what he did?

285
00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:28.573
He took care of me.

286
00:16:30.617 --> 00:16:34.663
He tucked me in...
[inhales sharply] ...and then he left.

287
00:16:35.455 --> 00:16:38.833
[John]
<i>I was technically working. Still am.</i>

288
00:16:40.085 --> 00:16:42.170
[Melanie]
And. um... And this morning when I woke up.

289
00:16:42.170 --> 00:16:43.922
I was struck by the possibility

290
00:16:43.922 --> 00:16:47.425
that this man might have been sent
to me by my Higher Power.

291
00:16:49.344 --> 00:16:50.887
Or he's just a decent guy.

292
00:16:53.181 --> 00:16:54.683
Or he's gay.

293
00:16:54.683 --> 00:16:57.435
- [chuckling]
- [Melanie] Ha ha. [chuckles]

294
00:16:58.562 --> 00:17:02.816
But. you know.
it-it doesn't matter what he was or is.

295
00:17:04.234 --> 00:17:06.570
What matters is how he made me feel.

296
00:17:06.570 --> 00:17:11.658
and he made me feel like I deserve
a second chance.

297
00:17:12.284 --> 00:17:14.202
So. thanks.

298
00:17:15.286 --> 00:17:17.080
[group applauding]

299
00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:25.005
{\an8}[Melanie] Thanks for coming.

300
00:17:25.630 --> 00:17:26.631
Thanks for asking me.

301
00:17:27.340 --> 00:17:29.426
- You want to talk about Olivia?
- I do.

302
00:17:29.926 --> 00:17:32.846
[clicks tongue] Ah. I'm still hungover.
You wanna get some food?

303
00:17:32.846 --> 00:17:34.306
- Sure.
- Can I get a ride?

304
00:17:34.306 --> 00:17:35.390
- Uh-huh.
- Good.

305
00:17:40.729 --> 00:17:44.608
When I woke up. I dumped all the booze.
so sparkling water is all you get.

306
00:17:44.608 --> 00:17:46.693
- That's fine.
- Yeah... [sighs] ...I know.

307
00:17:46.693 --> 00:17:47.903
You can't get drunk.

308
00:17:49.321 --> 00:17:51.740
- You remembered.
- Yeah. that I will never forget.

309
00:17:53.992 --> 00:17:57.370
So. yesterday.
were you following me. John Sugar...

310
00:17:57.370 --> 00:18:01.333
- No. No. complete coincidence.
- ...private investigator? No? Mmm.

311
00:18:01.333 --> 00:18:04.044
I was just following another lead.

312
00:18:04.044 --> 00:18:05.212
Oh. this one.

313
00:18:05.754 --> 00:18:06.880
- Yeah. that's the one.
- Yeah.

314
00:18:06.880 --> 00:18:09.716
Well. if you wanted to talk about Olivia.
you could have just asked.

315
00:18:09.716 --> 00:18:12.344
I'm not sure I would have believed
everything you said last night.

316
00:18:12.344 --> 00:18:14.763
I hate to break it to you.
Drunk. I'm an open book.

317
00:18:14.763 --> 00:18:16.139
Sober. I'm cagey as hell.

318
00:18:17.015 --> 00:18:19.100
You feel the need to be cagey
when it comes to Olivia?

319
00:18:19.100 --> 00:18:20.185
I didn't say that.

320
00:18:20.185 --> 00:18:21.478
Can I ask you a question?

321
00:18:22.020 --> 00:18:25.023
Why was she here almost every night
the week before she disappeared?

322
00:18:25.607 --> 00:18:27.108
What makes you think she was here?

323
00:18:27.108 --> 00:18:29.069
- I know she was here.
- How do you know?

324
00:18:29.569 --> 00:18:31.863
- GPS system in her car keeps a record.
- Oh.

325
00:18:31.863 --> 00:18:33.657
[chuckles]
How do you know she was driving?

326
00:18:33.657 --> 00:18:35.992
How do you know
a friend didn't take her car? [laughs]

327
00:18:37.327 --> 00:18:38.453
Is that what happened?

328
00:18:43.541 --> 00:18:45.377
I guess this is what you call being cagey. huh?

329
00:18:45.377 --> 00:18:46.628
Mmm.

330
00:18:46.628 --> 00:18:48.713
[buzzing]

331
00:18:49.422 --> 00:18:52.717
Well. I've been through most
of Olivia's social media posts

332
00:18:52.717 --> 00:18:53.802
over the past six months.

333
00:18:53.802 --> 00:18:56.012
And it's mostly pretty normal stuff.

334
00:18:56.930 --> 00:18:59.516
but it changed when you two
started spending more time together.

335
00:19:00.809 --> 00:19:02.060
You know. her focus. it shifted.

336
00:19:02.060 --> 00:19:04.854
- It turned to women's rights issues.
- What... What's wrong with that?

337
00:19:04.854 --> 00:19:06.356
No. not a... not a thing.

338
00:19:06.940 --> 00:19:10.026
[stammers] I think she finally found
something she was passionate about.

339
00:19:11.444 --> 00:19:13.780
But two weeks ago.
when she disappeared. well.

340
00:19:13.780 --> 00:19:15.949
her online presence disappeared also.
and that's concerning.

341
00:19:15.949 --> 00:19:18.743
Well. when you're talking about an addict.
there's a reason for a shift in behavior.

342
00:19:18.743 --> 00:19:21.955
She's probably using again. [sighs]
Look. i-it...

343
00:19:21.955 --> 00:19:23.999
She's probably gonna walk in here
any day now.

344
00:19:23.999 --> 00:19:28.378
just hungover and strung out
and ready to get back to rehab.

345
00:19:29.963 --> 00:19:30.964
That's funny.

346
00:19:31.840 --> 00:19:33.675
Your ex-husband told me the same thing
this morning.

347
00:19:33.675 --> 00:19:35.594
using almost exactly the same words.

348
00:19:37.053 --> 00:19:40.098
[John]
<i>Of course. he did. Circling the wagons.</i>

349
00:19:40.098 --> 00:19:42.893
Yeah. well. he called me
after you had breakfast with him.

350
00:19:43.977 --> 00:19:47.355
Bernie was a terrible husband.
but he's always been a great friend.

351
00:19:47.355 --> 00:19:48.523
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

352
00:19:50.817 --> 00:19:53.904
- [John] <i>That hair touch. that's her tell.</i>
- Look at this.

353
00:19:54.654 --> 00:19:56.865
I need you to tell me
if you've ever seen this man.

354
00:20:00.201 --> 00:20:02.996
Melanie. if you're in trouble
or if you know Olivia's in trouble.

355
00:20:02.996 --> 00:20:05.040
I can help. Just tell me what happened.

356
00:20:07.375 --> 00:20:09.502
I've never seen that man before
in my life.

357
00:20:09.502 --> 00:20:11.213
- Why are you doing this?
- Doing what?

358
00:20:11.213 --> 00:20:13.089
This. Your little act. I...

359
00:20:14.174 --> 00:20:16.593
I know you're lying.
I just can't figure out why.

360
00:20:18.261 --> 00:20:19.512
Maybe you're hiding something.

361
00:20:20.013 --> 00:20:21.223
[chuckles] Like what?

362
00:20:21.223 --> 00:20:22.390
Like where she is.

363
00:20:23.934 --> 00:20:25.852
Or where her body can be found.

364
00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:29.481
Get out of my house.

365
00:20:29.481 --> 00:20:34.569
I know you think you're helping her.
but you're doing her more harm than good.

366
00:20:34.569 --> 00:20:36.696
- Okay. get out of my house.
- Let me make this clear.

367
00:20:36.696 --> 00:20:38.782
I will find Olivia.

368
00:20:39.741 --> 00:20:41.201
It's what I do.

369
00:20:41.868 --> 00:20:43.078
I'm very good at it.

370
00:20:44.412 --> 00:20:45.580
[Melanie chuckles]

371
00:20:47.874 --> 00:20:48.875
Now.

372
00:21:04.182 --> 00:21:05.183
[John] <i>Hey. Charlie.</i>

373
00:21:05.725 --> 00:21:08.645
I think she knows where the girl is.
and she'll take us there tomorrow.

374
00:21:08.645 --> 00:21:10.230
Let's get the van ready. yeah?

375
00:21:10.814 --> 00:21:13.024
I'll see you in the morning.
All right. Bye.

376
00:21:23.868 --> 00:21:26.204
<i>You know.
I think that movies are a conspiracy.</i>

377
00:21:26.746 --> 00:21:27.789
<i>I mean it.</i>

378
00:21:28.415 --> 00:21:32.627
<i>They are actually a conspiracy
because they set you up. Florence.</i>

379
00:21:32.627 --> 00:21:35.672
<i>They set you up
from the time you're a little kid.</i>

380
00:21:36.172 --> 00:21:38.717
<i>They set you up to believe in everything.</i>

381
00:21:38.717 --> 00:21:45.223
<i>In ideals and strength
and good guys and. of course. love.</i>

382
00:21:46.850 --> 00:21:51.646
[chuckles] <i>But there's no Charles Boyer
in my life. Florence.</i>

383
00:21:51.646 --> 00:21:55.108
<i>I never met Clark Gable.
I never met Humphrey Bogart.</i>

384
00:21:55.108 --> 00:21:56.735
<i>I never... I never met any of them.</i>

385
00:21:56.735 --> 00:21:58.028
- <i>You know who I mean.</i>
- [Florence stammers]

386
00:21:58.028 --> 00:22:00.530
[actress] <i>I mean. they don't exist.
Florence. That's the truth.</i>

387
00:22:12.918 --> 00:22:14.044
[John] <i>That car again.</i>

388
00:22:15.503 --> 00:22:17.047
<i>Someone keeping an eye on me.</i>

389
00:22:17.547 --> 00:22:19.382
<i>On and off. keeping their distance.</i>

390
00:22:19.883 --> 00:22:23.678
[chuckles] <i>They're pretty good.
but I see 'em.</i>

391
00:22:29.851 --> 00:22:31.853
[car horn honking]

392
00:22:38.068 --> 00:22:40.570
[person] Hey! Hey! Hey!

393
00:22:46.284 --> 00:22:47.285
[John] Carl?

394
00:22:48.119 --> 00:22:49.120
Wiley.

395
00:22:50.205 --> 00:22:51.539
Hey. anyone seen Carl?

396
00:22:53.250 --> 00:22:55.794
- Tall guy. Blond hair. A-Anyone? Carl.
- No.

397
00:22:56.545 --> 00:22:59.798
- [clicks tongue] Carl!
- [person] Get the hell out of here. man.

398
00:23:01.007 --> 00:23:03.385
[line ringing]

399
00:23:05.053 --> 00:23:07.097
- [line beeps]
- [automated voice] <i>We're sorry.</i>

400
00:23:07.097 --> 00:23:08.265
- <i>You have reached a number...</i>
- Shit.

401
00:23:08.265 --> 00:23:09.933
- <i>...that has been disconnected.</i>
- Come here. Come here.

402
00:23:10.725 --> 00:23:13.770
In you go. Come on. Attaboy. Attaboy.

403
00:23:30.120 --> 00:23:31.705
[John] <i>I know. I know.</i>

404
00:23:32.497 --> 00:23:33.623
<i>What do I care?</i>

405
00:23:34.416 --> 00:23:35.917
<i>What business is this of mine?</i>

406
00:23:37.544 --> 00:23:40.714
<i>Yeah.
I often ask myself the same question.</i>

407
00:23:44.759 --> 00:23:46.761
[grunts] All right.

408
00:23:54.603 --> 00:23:55.770
[whining]

409
00:23:57.063 --> 00:23:59.065
[Wiley panting]

410
00:24:38.897 --> 00:24:40.148
Goddamn it. Carl.

411
00:24:43.235 --> 00:24:45.320
[toilet flushes]

412
00:24:49.074 --> 00:24:50.450
Who the fuck are you?

413
00:24:50.450 --> 00:24:51.660
What did you give him?

414
00:24:55.705 --> 00:24:56.831
What did you give him?

415
00:24:59.084 --> 00:25:00.460
Fuck off.

416
00:25:00.460 --> 00:25:02.170
[both grunting]

417
00:25:03.672 --> 00:25:05.006
[grunting]

418
00:25:06.174 --> 00:25:07.133
Hey!

419
00:25:07.133 --> 00:25:08.927
[gasping]

420
00:25:14.641 --> 00:25:16.101
[grunts. coughs]

421
00:25:16.101 --> 00:25:20.272
- [John] <i>I don't like hurting people.</i>
- [drug dealer coughing]

422
00:25:20.272 --> 00:25:21.356
[John] <i>I really don't.</i>

423
00:25:22.023 --> 00:25:24.192
[drug dealer grunting. coughing]

424
00:25:27.904 --> 00:25:29.573
[coughing]

425
00:25:33.201 --> 00:25:34.202
I was never here.

426
00:25:37.205 --> 00:25:38.832
<i>But this is what I mean.</i> [stammers]

427
00:25:38.832 --> 00:25:42.043
<i>A drug overdose. Happens every day.</i>

428
00:25:43.128 --> 00:25:44.462
<i>Why do I care?</i>

429
00:25:45.881 --> 00:25:51.803
[sighs] <i>Why do I feel angry?
Why do I feel anything at all?</i>

430
00:25:53.013 --> 00:25:55.515
- [sighs]
- [Wiley whines]

431
00:25:59.477 --> 00:26:01.062
- [whistles]
- [barks]

432
00:26:26.963 --> 00:26:28.340
- [John] Hey.
- Hi.

433
00:26:28.924 --> 00:26:30.675
You're interrupting my bridge club.

434
00:26:31.176 --> 00:26:34.429
Ah. right. Tuesday night bridge. Fun.

435
00:26:34.429 --> 00:26:36.389
[chuckles] All right. Good night. John.

436
00:26:36.389 --> 00:26:37.682
[John] Can I come in?

437
00:26:38.683 --> 00:26:41.144
Is there something urgent
regarding the Siegel case?

438
00:26:41.144 --> 00:26:44.773
No. No. not really. No. I-I. um...

439
00:26:47.817 --> 00:26:48.985
[meows]

440
00:26:48.985 --> 00:26:50.862
- He needs a place to stay.
- John.

441
00:26:52.405 --> 00:26:53.740
[meows]

442
00:26:53.740 --> 00:26:56.201
- [Wiley barks]
- This is Mirembe's house.

443
00:26:57.452 --> 00:26:58.995
- [barks]
- [Mirembe hisses]

444
00:26:59.537 --> 00:27:01.039
And Mirembe only has one rule.

445
00:27:01.539 --> 00:27:02.916
- No dogs.
- Yeah.

446
00:27:03.416 --> 00:27:04.417
Okay.

447
00:27:05.418 --> 00:27:07.254
Oh. uh... [stammers] ...gray Volkswagen.

448
00:27:08.463 --> 00:27:09.548
[stammers] What?

449
00:27:09.548 --> 00:27:13.635
Today I was being tailed by a gray VW.
You got any idea who that might be?

450
00:27:14.302 --> 00:27:17.055
Do you think it could be the Siegels.
like. keeping tabs on you?

451
00:27:17.055 --> 00:27:19.015
No. I... I think it was someone else.

452
00:27:21.726 --> 00:27:23.979
Did you take care of our friend
in the trunk?

453
00:27:28.233 --> 00:27:30.068
- Do it.
- [Mirembe meows]

454
00:27:30.944 --> 00:27:32.571
- [whining]
- [John] Come on. Wiley.

455
00:27:33.196 --> 00:27:35.490
Big mistake. They could have been friends.

456
00:27:38.159 --> 00:27:39.452
[Wiley barking]

457
00:27:45.709 --> 00:27:50.630
He just left. He said he was being tailed.
No. obviously they are watching him.

458
00:28:03.101 --> 00:28:06.104
[beeping. chimes]

459
00:28:11.109 --> 00:28:12.360
I'll be a son of a bitch.

460
00:28:16.197 --> 00:28:17.490
[John] <i>So much for body disposal.</i>

461
00:28:19.576 --> 00:28:20.702
<i>Someone beat me to it.</i>

462
00:28:42.891 --> 00:28:44.059
[Bernie] What am I looking at?

463
00:28:44.059 --> 00:28:46.561
[David] Magazines about movies.
Movies I never heard of.

464
00:28:46.561 --> 00:28:49.189
- Movies nobody's ever heard of.
- [Bernie] Mm-hmm.

465
00:28:51.816 --> 00:28:52.817
What are these?

466
00:28:53.443 --> 00:28:54.778
Letters from his mother. sir.

467
00:28:54.778 --> 00:28:56.821
[David] Yeah. here. [chuckles]

468
00:28:56.821 --> 00:28:57.906
You took this?

469
00:28:59.199 --> 00:29:00.617
What? He already read it.

470
00:29:00.617 --> 00:29:02.786
- [Bernie sighs] Next time. Davy...
- David.

471
00:29:02.786 --> 00:29:07.540
Next time. David.
let Kenny take his pictures. okay?

472
00:29:08.333 --> 00:29:10.335
All right. What the hell is this?

473
00:29:10.335 --> 00:29:11.670
[David] Uh. an invitation.

474
00:29:11.670 --> 00:29:14.047
Yeah. [stammers]
I can see that. but to what?

475
00:29:14.047 --> 00:29:16.925
I don't know. I... [stammers] I googled it.
I... I couldn't find anything.

476
00:29:16.925 --> 00:29:19.052
[stammers] It doesn't
even have a location. Mr. Siegel.

477
00:29:19.052 --> 00:29:21.012
Just a date and time. Tomorrow night.

478
00:29:24.099 --> 00:29:25.225
What about the bug?

479
00:29:25.225 --> 00:29:27.519
Nothing. He must have found it.

480
00:29:28.311 --> 00:29:31.565
[sighs. stammers]
Listen to me and learn something.

481
00:29:31.565 --> 00:29:34.109
I think of my life as an ecosystem.

482
00:29:35.485 --> 00:29:37.362
- You know what that is?
- Yes. I know what an ecosystem is.

483
00:29:37.362 --> 00:29:39.281
[Bernie] Good. then pay attention.
Because in my ecosystem.

484
00:29:39.281 --> 00:29:43.535
there's me. there's my wife.
there's my children.

485
00:29:43.535 --> 00:29:45.161
and there's my production company.

486
00:29:45.870 --> 00:29:48.957
All I care about is my ecosystem.

487
00:29:48.957 --> 00:29:52.085
So when a foreign body comes into it.
I go on fucking high alert

488
00:29:52.085 --> 00:29:54.337
and I wonder.
"Is this a positive or a negative force?"

489
00:29:54.337 --> 00:29:59.259
And the only way I can truly answer that
is to truly understand the foreign body.

490
00:29:59.259 --> 00:30:03.096
The last thing we need is him
looking beyond Olivia to anyone else.

491
00:30:03.096 --> 00:30:04.180
like you. David.

492
00:30:05.807 --> 00:30:08.935
So. find out everything you can
about this Mr. John Sugar.

493
00:30:10.228 --> 00:30:11.104
Fuck yeah.

494
00:30:11.104 --> 00:30:13.565
- I want a report by tomorrow evening.
- [David] You got it. Dad.

495
00:30:31.333 --> 00:30:33.460
[John] <i>Clifford Carter and Carmen Vasquez.</i>

496
00:30:35.420 --> 00:30:39.925
<i>What's the connection to Olivia?
Why can't I see it?</i>

497
00:30:43.678 --> 00:30:45.347
<i>I'm not supposed to get this involved.</i>

498
00:30:53.396 --> 00:30:55.106
<i>Just observe and report.</i>

499
00:30:57.067 --> 00:30:58.401
<i>Write it down.</i>

500
00:31:00.237 --> 00:31:01.446
<i>That's the real mission.</i>

501
00:31:09.537 --> 00:31:11.081
<i>That's the idea anyways.</i>

502
00:31:14.167 --> 00:31:15.335
[glass thuds]

503
00:31:16.836 --> 00:31:18.838
<i>That's what Ruby keeps telling us...</i>

504
00:31:21.216 --> 00:31:22.425
<i>but I can't help it.</i>

505
00:31:25.220 --> 00:31:26.221
<i>I can't stop.</i>

506
00:31:28.723 --> 00:31:29.724
<i>I'm involved.</i>

507
00:31:31.726 --> 00:31:33.478
<i>She reminds me of Djen.</i>

508
00:31:35.188 --> 00:31:37.774
<i>I hope this case has a different ending.
But. yeah...</i>

509
00:31:41.278 --> 00:31:42.696
<i>she reminds me of my sister.</i>

510
00:31:42.696 --> 00:31:44.447
[family singing in Spanish]

511
00:31:45.198 --> 00:31:46.241
[John] <i>I'm gonna find her.</i>

512
00:31:47.158 --> 00:31:49.244
<i>She's out there somewhere.</i>

513
00:31:49.244 --> 00:31:53.707
[all singing in Spanish]

514
00:32:01.339 --> 00:32:05.176
[singing in Spanish. chuckling]

515
00:32:05.176 --> 00:32:07.679
[parent singing in Spanish. laughing]

516
00:32:07.679 --> 00:32:09.222
[gasps. screams]

517
00:32:09.723 --> 00:32:13.184
- [speaks Spanish]
- [burglar 1] No.

518
00:32:13.184 --> 00:32:15.687
No. no. no. Back in the apartment.

519
00:32:17.022 --> 00:32:18.398
[burglar 2] <i>Buenas noches</i>.

520
00:32:18.398 --> 00:32:20.400
- [whispering in Spanish]
- Teresa. right?

521
00:32:22.193 --> 00:32:24.863
So. she's gonna take the kids
into the bedroom...

522
00:32:24.863 --> 00:32:26.990
- [both speak Spanish]
- ...to watch some television.

523
00:32:28.491 --> 00:32:30.869
Or I will give them to him.

524
00:32:32.078 --> 00:32:33.788
[burglar 3] Come on.
Let's go watch a movie.

525
00:32:33.788 --> 00:32:37.208
<i>Ándele.</i> Okay? [speaks Spanish]

526
00:32:37.208 --> 00:32:40.962
[burglar 2] So. Teresa. uh.
I'm looking for my friend. [sighs]

527
00:32:41.713 --> 00:32:43.924
Clifford Carter.
He was fucking your sister.

528
00:32:46.259 --> 00:32:47.260
I don't know him.

529
00:32:47.761 --> 00:32:49.221
[burglar 2] Don't lie to me. Teresa.

530
00:32:50.222 --> 00:32:51.473
All right. I'll give you one of those.

531
00:32:51.473 --> 00:32:55.101
But if you lie to me again. I'm gonna
punch you really hard in the face.

532
00:32:56.186 --> 00:32:57.812
Deal? [inhales sharply]

533
00:32:57.812 --> 00:32:59.439
Hey. Clifford's my main man.

534
00:33:00.148 --> 00:33:04.486
You know. he knows things about me and my
clients I don't want anybody else knowing.

535
00:33:05.320 --> 00:33:08.657
And he stored all this shit... my shit...
on his phone.

536
00:33:08.657 --> 00:33:14.537
But now I haven't seen or heard
from Clifford in over two weeks.

537
00:33:17.457 --> 00:33:18.458
Makes me nervous.

538
00:33:20.794 --> 00:33:22.128
Can you understand that?

539
00:33:23.255 --> 00:33:24.256
Yes.

540
00:33:25.173 --> 00:33:28.176
[burglar 2] This was the last text he sent
before he disappeared.

541
00:33:30.178 --> 00:33:31.638
{\an8}It's your sister Carmen. right?

542
00:33:34.349 --> 00:33:36.434
- Yes.
- [burglar 2 chuckles]

543
00:33:36.434 --> 00:33:39.354
Took me two weeks to figure out
who this bitch was.

544
00:33:43.400 --> 00:33:46.194
So. obviously. in a perfect world
we'd be talking to Carmen

545
00:33:46.194 --> 00:33:47.821
about what the hell happened
to our main man.

546
00:33:47.821 --> 00:33:50.365
But it's not a perfect world
because she's dead.

547
00:33:50.365 --> 00:33:54.160
But we can talk to you. right. Teresa?

548
00:33:56.121 --> 00:33:57.706
- Yes.
- Yeah.

549
00:33:59.291 --> 00:34:02.544
So. this is the text he sent after that.

550
00:34:03.879 --> 00:34:05.755
You have any idea who this is?

551
00:34:19.227 --> 00:34:21.061
- [Teresa cries]
- Thank you.

552
00:34:22.355 --> 00:34:23.606
Thank you. Thank you.

553
00:34:23.606 --> 00:34:25.442
- She... She knows.
- [sighs deeply]

554
00:34:26.276 --> 00:34:27.527
We'll talk to her next.
